---
title: Scenario 8 — Page Navigation While Animation In Flight
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Box as AnimatedListBox
    participant Pipeline as Pipeline
    participant Anim as In-Flight Animation
    participant PageCmd as NextPageCommand

    Note over Box: User is on page 1\nOrder change FLIP animating

    Box->>Anim: FLIP running\n_inflightCount = 3\n_pipelineBusy = true

    Note over Anim: ~100ms into 200ms FLIP

    User->>PageCmd: Click ▶ (NextPageCommand)
    PageCmd->>Box: CurrentPage++ → CurrentPageProperty.Changed fires
    Box->>Box: OnCurrentPageChanged()

    Note over Box: Page navigation is ALWAYS instant\nBypasses the pipeline entirely

    Box->>Box: SnapAllAnimations()
    Note over Anim: All CTSes cancelled\nContainers snapped to (0,0) / opacity 1\nGhosts removed from VisibleItems\n_flipGeneration++ (stale FLIP discarded if pending)\n_inflightCount reset via CTS cancellation paths

    Box->>Pipeline: _pipeline.Clear() — discard all queued work\n_batchGeneration++ — invalidate stale OnBatchComplete\n_pipelineBusy = false

    Box->>Box: UpdatePageCount(full)\nCurrentPage = 2

    Box->>Box: ReplaceVisible(page2items)
    Note over Box: VisibleItems.Clear() fires\nClearContainerForItemOverride for all containers\nThen new items inserted\nPrepareContainerForItemOverride fires\nNo entry animation (not animated path)

    Note over Box: Page 2 items appear instantly\nNo animation, no artifacts

    Note over Box: If a stale OnBatchComplete fires from\nthe cancelled FLIP timer/counter...
    Anim-->>Box: OnBatchComplete (stale — from cancelled animation)
    Box->>Box: Check _batchGeneration\ncapturedGeneration != _batchGeneration\n→ return, do nothing

    Note over Box: Result: Clean instant page change\nno matter what was animating
